nd that existing tests in another module can still import from the plugin. Finally, there's a potential issue with Checkstyle line length, and I need to decide if I need to run it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing code style**\\n\\nI’m inspecting the style of the code, particularly looking at the maximum line length, which might be set to 120. I see that the static result could already exceed that. H2Test has some longer lines too. I should check if Checkstyle is strict on this. There's one line with `loadedClass = ...` that’s definitely longer than 120 characters. I need to edit those long lines for readability. I'll also think about using read lines with newline characters.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ynwLcz5eMDSUDuL7hzX805bk|fc_0e2d68cd0bedd6630169f4cc8a9e1081a1be697ec41f5a0da4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/UtilsTest.java')\nfor i,l in enumerate(p.read_text().splitlines(),1):\n    if len(l)>120:\n        print(i,len(l),l)\nPY"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\np=Path('tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/UtilsTest.java')\\nfor i,l in enumerate(p.read_text().splitlines(),1):\\n    if len(l)>120:\\n        print(i,len(l),l)\\nPY\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2026, "output": 686, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46744, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777650810327, "responseId": "resp_0e2d68cd0bedd6630169f4cc7ad56481a18bbe9def7376ce3e"}}
